<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · What we service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Premium wood-fired Naples-style ovens, 600 to 900°F dome temperatures.</h2>

    <p>Wood-fired pizza ovens are the premium tier of LA Italian and Neapolitan dining. Refractory dome architecture, traditional 600 to 900°F continuous operation, $25,000 to $100,000+ installed. Used in upscale Italian restaurants across Beverly Hills, West Hollywood, Pasadena, Pacific Palisades, plus craft Italian chains.</p>

    <p>Four brands cover the LA premium wood-fired market: <strong>Forno Bravo</strong> (independent California, modular dome, Casa series, Professionale 110 and Professionale 130 most common), <strong>Wood Stone</strong> (independent Washington state, dominant US wood-fired commercial, Mountain Series and Fire Deck gas-assist), <strong>Marra Forni</strong> (Italian premium, Rotator deck variants), <strong>Pavesi</strong> (Italian premium, Capri 120 series).</p>

    <p>Wood-fired oven repair is a specialty trade that most appliance shops decline. Limited mechanical components (mostly refractory dome plus floor stone plus damper plus thermometer plus optional gas-assist component), specialty diagnostic, SCAQMD compliance awareness for LA-area commercial wood-burning operations. Our techs handle it.</p>

    <p><strong>SCAQMD note.</strong> South Coast Air Quality Management District has rules on commercial wood-burning equipment in LA, Orange, Riverside, and San Bernardino counties. Pre-existing installs typically grandfathered, new installs face stricter requirements. Wood Stone Fire Deck offers gas-assist versions for compliance: wood-fire taste with gas temperature control. We document your compliance status and refer to SCAQMD compliance specialists if needed.</p>

    <p>This is not a deck pizza oven (Bakers Pride Y, Marsal, completely different platform, see <a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/deck-pizza-oven-repair/">deck pizza oven repair</a>) and not a conveyor pizza oven (Lincoln Impinger, Middleby Marshall, see <a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/conveyor-pizza-oven-repair/">conveyor pizza oven repair</a>).</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong>. <strong>EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410</strong>. CSLB C-20 HVAC and C-38 Refrigeration scope. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7, no emergency surcharge.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Typical wood-fired oven failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Wood-fired ovens have fewer failure modes than gas decks, but the ones they have are big.</h2>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Refractory dome cracking (year 10 to 15+).</strong> Thermal cycling fatigue eventually cracks the dome. Minor cracks ($800 to $1,800 with specialty masonry referral coordination) versus major dome damage ($3,000 to $8,000+). We document the crack pattern, refer to specialty refractory contractors, recommission post-repair.</li>
      <li><strong>Floor stone wear or replacement.</strong> Heavy use over 10+ years wears the refractory floor where peels slide pizzas in and out. Replacement is specialty refractory work, typically $2,400 to $4,000.</li>
      <li><strong>Damper actuator (chimney damper).</strong> Mechanical wear on the damper opens-and-closes mechanism. Service-call repair, $480 to $780.</li>
      <li><strong>Dome thermometer or pyrometer.</strong> Surface-mount temperature sensor wears or drifts. $260 to $440 replacement plus calibration.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas burner (gas-assist models, Wood Stone Fire Deck and some Forno Bravo Professionale).</strong> Standard gas-burner service: igniter, thermocouple, gas valve. $440 to $980.</li>
      <li><strong>Igniter (gas-assist).</strong> $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Rotator drive motor (Marra Forni Rotator deck).</strong> Mechanical drive that rotates the deck under the dome. Year 8 to 12 typical wear. $1,200 to $1,800.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
