    <h2 class="section-title">Real repair stories from the last few weeks.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Composite examples; model numbers, ages, and prices are accurate to typical scope.</p>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Beverly Hills · Forno Bravo Professionale 110, 12 years old</h3>
      <p>Italian restaurant. Naples-style 110cm dome. Refractory floor showing heavy wear at peel-entry zone, customer complaints about pies sticking. Documented wear, coordinated with specialty refractory contractor for floor stone replacement (manufacturer-spec refractory blend), recommissioned oven, verified dome temp recovery. Total: $120 plus $3,080 specialty refractory work plus 2 hours commissioning = $3,200.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>West Hollywood · Wood Stone Fire Deck 9645 gas-assist, 8 years old</h3>
      <p>Pizzeria. Gas-assist component not lighting reliably (slow dome warm-up, longer wood-fire startup). Diagnosed: gas-assist burner ignition module failing, plus thermocouple weak. Replaced burner igniter and thermocouple. Verified gas-assist startup and steady-state operation. Total: $120 plus $720 parts plus 1.5 hours = $1,400.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Pacific Palisades · Marra Forni Rotator deck, 9 years old</h3>
      <p>Premium restaurant. Rotator drive motor seized, pies cooking unevenly because operator was rotating manually. Replaced rotator drive motor, replaced dome thermometer (drifted past calibration tolerance after years). Total: $120 plus $1,580 motor plus $360 thermometer plus 2.5 hours = $2,200.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Pasadena · Pavesi Capri 120, 14 years old</h3>
      <p>Italian chain location. Refractory dome crack documented (lateral hairline, opens slightly under thermal load), damper actuator stuck partially closed. Coordinated with specialty refractory contractor for crack repair (specialty masonry trade), replaced damper actuator. Major repair. Total: $120 plus $4,200 dome crack repair (specialty referral) plus $480 damper plus 2 hours commissioning = $4,800.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for wood-fired ovens, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service directly:</strong> gas-assist burner components (Wood Stone Fire Deck and Forno Bravo Professionale gas-assist variants), igniter, thermocouple, gas valve, damper actuator, dome thermometer, pyrometer, rotator drive motor (Marra Forni Rotator), commissioning and dome temperature verification post-repair.</p>

    <p><strong>We coordinate (specialty referral):</strong> refractory dome crack repair, floor stone replacement, dome rebuild. Heavy refractory work requires specific masonry equipment and certifications we don't carry. We document the failure, refer to specialty refractory contractors, recommission the oven post-repair, document for your records.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> deck pizza ovens on this page (see <a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/deck-pizza-oven-repair/">deck pizza oven repair</a>); conveyor pizza ovens (see <a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/conveyor-pizza-oven-repair/">conveyor pizza oven repair</a>); new wood-fired oven installation (specialty installer trade requiring SCAQMD permit coordination); SCAQMD permit application work (specialty environmental compliance trade); chimney masonry (separate masonry trade); Type I hood work above the oven (see <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/">commercial exhaust hood repair</a>).</p>
  </div>
</section>

